#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="mn130"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn130:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 130 "
msgstr "Middle Discourses 130 "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn130:0.2"
msgid "Devadūtasutta "
msgstr "Messengers of the Gods "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: nya1, sc1
msgctxt "mn130:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "mn130:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. "

msgctxt "mn130:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants, "

msgctxt "mn130:1.4"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti. "
msgstr "“Mendicants!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn130:1.5"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ. "
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied. "

msgctxt "mn130:1.6"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "The Buddha said this: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya2, pts-vp-pli3.179, sc2
#. VAR: sadvārā → sandhidvārā (mr)
msgctxt "mn130:2.1"
msgid "“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, dve agārā sadvārā, tattha cakkhumā puriso majjhe ṭhito passeyya manusse gehaṃ pavisantepi nikkhamantepi anucaṅkamantepi anuvicarantepi; "
msgstr "“Mendicants, suppose there were two houses with doors. A person with good eyesight standing in between them would see people entering and leaving a house and wandering to and fro. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn130:2.2"
msgid "evameva kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passāmi cavamāne upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe, sugate duggate yathākammūpage satte pajānāmi: ‘ime vata bhonto sattā kāyasucaritena samannāgatā vacīsucaritena samannāgatā manosucaritena samannāgatā ariyānaṃ anupavādakā sammādiṭṭhikā sammādiṭṭhikammasamādānā; te kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapannā. Ime vā pana bhonto sattā kāyasucaritena samannāgatā vacīsucaritena samannāgatā manosucaritena samannāgatā ariyānaṃ anupavādakā sammādiṭṭhikā sammādiṭṭhikammasamādānā; te kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā manussesu upapannā. Ime vata bhonto sattā kāyaduccaritena samannāgatā vacīduccaritena samannāgatā manoduccaritena samannāgatā ariyānaṃ upavādakā micchādiṭṭhikā micchādiṭṭhikammasamādānā; te kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā pettivisayaṃ upapannā. Ime vā pana bhonto sattā kāyaduccaritena samannāgatā vacīduccaritena samannāgatā manoduccaritena samannāgatā ariyānaṃ upavādakā micchādiṭṭhikā micchādiṭṭhikammasamādānā; te kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā tiracchānayoniṃ upapannā. Ime vā pana bhonto sattā kāyaduccaritena samannāgatā vacīduccaritena samannāgatā manoduccaritena samannāgatā ariyānaṃ upavādakā micchādiṭṭhikā micchādiṭṭhikammasamādānā; te kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapannā’ti. "
msgstr "In the same way, with clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, I see sentient beings passing away and being reborn—inferior and superior, beautiful and ugly, in a good place or a bad place. I understand how sentient beings are reborn according to their deeds: ‘These dear beings did good things by way of body, speech, and mind. They never spoke ill of the noble ones; they had right view; and they chose to act out of that right view. When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm, or among humans. These dear beings did bad things by way of body, speech, and mind. They spoke ill of the noble ones; they had wrong view; and they chose to act out of that wrong view. When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in the ghost realm, the animal realm, or in a lower realm, a bad destination, a world of misery, hell.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya3, sc3
msgctxt "mn130:3.1"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, nirayapālā nānābāhāsu gahetvā yamassa rañño dassenti: "
msgstr "Then the wardens of hell take them by the arms and present them to King Yama, saying, "

msgctxt "mn130:3.2"
msgid "‘ayaṃ, deva, puriso amatteyyo apetteyyo asāmañño abrāhmañño, na kule jeṭṭhāpacāyī. "
msgstr "‘Your Majesty, this person did not pay due respect to their mother and father, ascetics and brahmins, or honor the elders in the family. "

msgctxt "mn130:3.3"
msgid "Imassa devo daṇḍaṃ paṇetū’ti. "
msgstr "May Your Majesty punish them!’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn130:3.4"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, yamo rājā paṭhamaṃ devadūtaṃ samanuyuñjati samanugāhati samanubhāsati: "
msgstr "Then King Yama pursues, presses, and grills them about the first messenger of the gods. "

msgctxt "mn130:3.5"
msgid "‘ambho purisa, na tvaṃ addasa manussesu paṭhamaṃ devadūtaṃ pātubhūtan’ti? "
msgstr "‘Mister, did you not see the first messenger of the gods that appeared among human beings?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn130:3.6"
msgid "So evamāha: "
msgstr "He says, "

msgctxt "mn130:3.7"
msgid "‘nāddasaṃ, bhante’ti. "
msgstr "‘I saw nothing, sir.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya4, sc4
msgctxt "mn130:4.1"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, yamo rājā evamāha: "
msgstr "Then King Yama says, "

msgctxt "mn130:4.2"
msgid "‘ambho purisa, na tvaṃ addasa manussesu daharaṃ kumāraṃ mandaṃ uttānaseyyakaṃ sake muttakarīse palipannaṃ semānan’ti? "
msgstr "‘Mister, did you not see among human beings a little baby collapsed in their own urine and feces?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn130:4.3"
msgid "So evamāha: "
msgstr "He says, "

msgctxt "mn130:4.4"
msgid "‘addasaṃ, bhante’ti. "
msgstr "‘I saw that, sir.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "mn130:4.5"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, yamo rājā evamāha: "
msgstr "Then King Yama says, "

msgctxt "mn130:4.6"
msgid "‘ambho purisa, tassa te viññussa sato mahallakassa na etadahosi—"
msgstr "‘Mister, did it not occur to you—being sensible and mature—"

msgctxt "mn130:4.7"
msgid "ahampi khomhi jātidhammo, jātiṃ anatīto. Handāhaṃ kalyāṇaṃ karomi kāyena vācāya manasā’ti? "
msgstr "“I, too, am liable to be born. I’m not exempt from rebirth. I’d better do good by way of body, speech, and mind”?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn130:4.8"
msgid "So evamāha: "
msgstr "He says, "

msgctxt "mn130:4.9"
msgid "‘nāsakkhissaṃ, bhante, pamādassaṃ, bhante’ti. "
msgstr "‘I couldn’t, sir. I was negligent.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.180, sc6
msgctxt "mn130:4.10"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, yamo rājā evamāha: "
msgstr "Then King Yama says, "

msgctxt "mn130:4.11"
msgid "‘ambho purisa, pamādavatāya na kalyāṇamakāsi kāyena vācāya manasā. "
msgstr "‘Mister, because you were negligent, you didn’t do good by way of body, speech, and mind. "

msgctxt "mn130:4.12"
msgid "Taggha tvaṃ, ambho purisa, tathā karissanti yathā taṃ pamattaṃ. "
msgstr "Well, they’ll definitely punish you to fit your negligence. "

#. VAR: pāpakammaṃ → pāpaṃ kammaṃ (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "mn130:4.13"
msgid "Taṃ kho pana te etaṃ pāpakammaṃ neva mātarā kataṃ na pitarā kataṃ na bhātarā kataṃ na bhaginiyā kataṃ na mittāmaccehi kataṃ na ñātisālohitehi kataṃ na samaṇabrāhmaṇehi kataṃ na devatāhi kataṃ, tayāvetaṃ pāpakammaṃ kataṃ, tvaññevetassa vipākaṃ paṭisaṃvedissasī’ti. (1) "
msgstr "That bad deed wasn’t done by your mother, father, brother, or sister. It wasn’t done by friends and colleagues, by relatives and kin, by ascetics and brahmins, or by the deities. That bad deed was done by you alone, and you alone will experience the result.’ "

