#. REF: nya8, sc19
msgctxt "mn130:8.1"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, yamo rājā catutthaṃ devadūtaṃ samanuyuñjitvā samanugāhitvā samanubhāsitvā pañcamaṃ devadūtaṃ samanuyuñjati samanugāhati samanubhāsati: "
msgstr "Then King Yama grills them about the fifth messenger of the gods. "

msgctxt "mn130:8.2"
msgid "‘ambho purisa, na tvaṃ addasa manussesu pañcamaṃ devadūtaṃ pātubhūtan’ti? "
msgstr "‘Mister, did you not see the fifth messenger of the gods that appeared among human beings?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn130:8.3"
msgid "So evamāha: "
msgstr "He says, "

msgctxt "mn130:8.4"
msgid "‘nāddasaṃ, bhante’ti. "
msgstr "‘I saw nothing, sir.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc20
msgctxt "mn130:8.5"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, yamo rājā evamāha: "
msgstr "Then King Yama says, "

msgctxt "mn130:8.6"
msgid "‘ambho purisa, na tvaṃ addasa manussesu itthiṃ vā purisaṃ vā ekāhamataṃ vā dvīhamataṃ vā tīhamataṃ vā uddhumātakaṃ vinīlakaṃ vipubbakajātan’ti? "
msgstr "‘Mister, did you not see among human beings a woman or a man, dead for one, two, or three days, bloated, livid, and festering?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn130:8.7"
msgid "So evamāha: "
msgstr "He says, "

msgctxt "mn130:8.8"
msgid "‘addasaṃ, bhante’ti. "
msgstr "‘I saw that, sir.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc21
msgctxt "mn130:8.9"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, yamo rājā evamāha: "
msgstr "Then King Yama says, "

msgctxt "mn130:8.10"
msgid "‘ambho purisa, tassa te viññussa sato mahallakassa na etadahosi—"
msgstr "‘Mister, did it not occur to you—being sensible and mature—"

msgctxt "mn130:8.11"
msgid "ahampi khomhi maraṇadhammo, maraṇaṃ anatīto. Handāhaṃ kalyāṇaṃ karomi kāyena vācāya manasā’ti? "
msgstr "“I, too, am liable to die. I’m not exempt from death. I’d better do good by way of body, speech, and mind”?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn130:8.12"
msgid "So evamāha: "
msgstr "He says, "

msgctxt "mn130:8.13"
msgid "‘nāsakkhissaṃ, bhante, pamādassaṃ, bhante’ti. "
msgstr "‘I couldn’t, sir. I was negligent.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc22
msgctxt "mn130:8.14"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, yamo rājā evamāha: "
msgstr "Then King Yama says, "

msgctxt "mn130:8.15"
msgid "‘ambho purisa, pamādavatāya na kalyāṇamakāsi kāyena vācāya manasā. "
msgstr "‘Mister, because you were negligent, you didn’t do good by way of body, speech, and mind. "

msgctxt "mn130:8.16"
msgid "Taggha tvaṃ, ambho purisa, tathā karissanti yathā taṃ pamattaṃ. "
msgstr "Well, they’ll definitely punish you to fit your negligence. "

msgctxt "mn130:8.17"
msgid "Taṃ kho pana te etaṃ pāpakammaṃ neva mātarā kataṃ na pitarā kataṃ na bhātarā kataṃ na bhaginiyā kataṃ na mittāmaccehi kataṃ na ñātisālohitehi kataṃ na samaṇabrāhmaṇehi kataṃ na devatāhi kataṃ, tayāvetaṃ pāpakammaṃ kataṃ, tvaññevetassa vipākaṃ paṭisaṃvedissasī’ti. (5) "
msgstr "That bad deed wasn’t done by your mother, father, brother, or sister. It wasn’t done by friends and colleagues, by relatives and kin, by ascetics and brahmins, or by the deities. That bad deed was done by you alone, and you alone will experience the result.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya9, pts-vp-pli3.183, sc23
msgctxt "mn130:9.1"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, yamo rājā pañcamaṃ devadūtaṃ samanuyuñjitvā samanugāhitvā samanubhāsitvā tuṇhī hoti. "
msgstr "Then, after grilling them about the fifth messenger of the gods, King Yama falls silent. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya10
msgctxt "mn130:10.1"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, nirayapālā pañcavidhabandhanaṃ nāma kammakāraṇaṃ karonti—"
msgstr "Then the wardens of hell punish them with the five-fold crucifixion. "

msgctxt "mn130:10.2"
msgid "tattaṃ ayokhilaṃ hatthe gamenti, tattaṃ ayokhilaṃ dutiye hatthe gamenti, tattaṃ ayokhilaṃ pāde gamenti, tattaṃ ayokhilaṃ dutiye pāde gamenti, tattaṃ ayokhilaṃ majjheurasmiṃ gamenti. "
msgstr "They drive red-hot stakes through the hands and feet, and another in the middle of the chest. "

msgctxt "mn130:10.3"
msgid "So tattha dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedeti, na ca tāva kālaṃ karoti yāva na taṃ pāpakammaṃ byantīhoti. "
msgstr "And there they feel painful, sharp, severe, acute feelings—but they don’t die until that bad deed is eliminated. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya11
msgctxt "mn130:11.1"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, nirayapālā saṃvesetvā kuṭhārīhi tacchanti … pe … "
msgstr "Then the wardens of hell throw them down and hack them with axes. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya12
msgctxt "mn130:12.1"
msgid "tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, nirayapālā uddhampādaṃ adhosiraṃ gahetvā vāsīhi tacchanti … pe … "
msgstr "They hang them upside-down and hack them with hatchets. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya13
msgctxt "mn130:13.1"
msgid "tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, nirayapālā rathe yojetvā ādittāya pathaviyā sampajjalitāya sajotibhūtāya sārentipi, paccāsārentipi … pe … "
msgstr "They harness them to a chariot, and drive them back and forth across burning ground, blazing and glowing. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya14
msgctxt "mn130:14.1"
msgid "tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, nirayapālā mahantaṃ aṅgārapabbataṃ ādittaṃ sampajjalitaṃ sajotibhūtaṃ āropentipi oropentipi … pe … "
msgstr "They make them climb up and down a huge mountain of burning coals, blazing and glowing. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya15
msgctxt "mn130:15.1"
msgid "tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, nirayapālā uddhampādaṃ adhosiraṃ gahetvā tattāya lohakumbhiyā pakkhipanti ādittāya sampajjalitāya sajotibhūtāya. "
msgstr "Then the wardens of hell turn them upside down and throw them in a red-hot copper pot, burning, blazing, and glowing. "

msgctxt "mn130:15.2"
msgid "So tattha pheṇuddehakaṃ paccati. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn130:15.3"
msgid "So tattha pheṇuddehakaṃ paccamāno sakimpi uddhaṃ gacchati, sakimpi adho gacchati, sakimpi tiriyaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr "There they’re seared in boiling scum, and they’re swept up and down and round and round. "

msgctxt "mn130:15.4"
msgid "So tattha dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedeti, na ca tāva kālaṃ karoti yāva na taṃ pāpakammaṃ byantīhoti. "
msgstr "And there they feel painful, sharp, severe, acute feelings—but they don’t die until that bad deed is eliminated. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya16
msgctxt "mn130:15.5"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, nirayapālā mahāniraye pakkhipanti. "
msgstr "Then the wardens of hell toss them into the Great Hell. "

msgctxt "mn130:15.6"
msgid "So kho pana, bhikkhave, mahānirayo—"
msgstr "Now, about that Great Hell: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc24
msgctxt "mn130:15.7"
msgid "Catukkaṇṇo catudvāro, "
msgstr "‘Four are its corners, four its doors, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn130:15.8"
msgid "vibhatto bhāgaso mito; "
msgstr "divided into measured parts. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn130:15.9"
msgid "Ayopākārapariyanto, "
msgstr "Surrounded by an iron wall, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn130:15.10"
msgid "ayasā paṭikujjito. "
msgstr "of iron is its roof. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc25
msgctxt "mn130:15.11"
msgid "Tassa ayomayā bhūmi, "
msgstr "The ground is even made of iron, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn130:15.12"
msgid "jalitā tejasāyutā; "
msgstr "it burns with fierce fire. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn130:15.13"
msgid "Samantā yojanasataṃ, "
msgstr "The heat forever radiates "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn130:15.14"
msgid "pharitvā tiṭṭhati sabbadā. "
msgstr "a hundred leagues around.’ "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: nya17, pts-vp-pli3.184, sc26
msgctxt "mn130:17.1"
msgid "Tassa kho pana, bhikkhave, mahānirayassa puratthimāya bhittiyā acci uṭṭhahitvā pacchimāya bhittiyā paṭihaññati, pacchimāya bhittiyā acci uṭṭhahitvā puratthimāya bhittiyā paṭihaññati, uttarāya bhittiyā acci uṭṭhahitvā dakkhiṇāya bhittiyā paṭihaññati, dakkhiṇāya bhittiyā acci uṭṭhahitvā uttarāya bhittiyā paṭihaññati, heṭṭhā acci uṭṭhahitvā upari paṭihaññati, uparito acci uṭṭhahitvā heṭṭhā paṭihaññati. "
msgstr "Now in the Great Hell, flames surge out of the walls and crash into the opposite wall: from east to west, from west to east, from north to south, from south to north, from bottom to top, from top to bottom. "

msgctxt "mn130:17.2"
msgid "So tattha dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedeti, na ca tāva kālaṃ karoti yāva na taṃ pāpakammaṃ byantīhoti. "
msgstr "And there they feel painful, sharp, severe, acute feelings—but they don’t die until that bad deed is eliminated. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya18, sc27
#. VAR: apāpurīyati → avāpurīyati (bj)
msgctxt "mn130:18.1"
msgid "Hoti kho so, bhikkhave, samayo yaṃ kadāci karahaci dīghassa addhuno accayena tassa mahānirayassa puratthimaṃ dvāraṃ apāpurīyati. "
msgstr "There comes a time when, after a very long period has passed, the eastern gate of the Great Hell is opened. "

msgctxt "mn130:18.2"
msgid "So tattha sīghena javena dhāvati. "
msgstr "So they run there as fast as they can. "

msgctxt "mn130:18.3"
msgid "Tassa sīghena javena dhāvato chavimpi ḍayhati, cammampi ḍayhati, maṃsampi ḍayhati, nhārumpi ḍayhati, aṭṭhīnipi sampadhūpāyanti, ubbhataṃ tādisameva hoti. "
msgstr "And as they run, their outer skin, inner skin, flesh, and sinews burn and even their bones smoke. Such is their escape; "

#. VAR: pidhīyati → pithīyati (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn130:18.4"
msgid "Yato ca kho so, bhikkhave, bahusampatto hoti, atha taṃ dvāraṃ pidhīyati. "
msgstr "but when they’ve managed to make it most of the way, the gate is slammed shut. "

msgctxt "mn130:18.5"
msgid "So tattha dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedeti, na ca tāva kālaṃ karoti yāva na taṃ pāpakammaṃ byantīhoti. "
msgstr "And there they feel painful, sharp, severe, acute feelings—but they don’t die until that bad deed is eliminated. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc28
msgctxt "mn130:18.6"
msgid "Hoti kho so, bhikkhave, samayo yaṃ kadāci karahaci dīghassa addhuno accayena tassa mahānirayassa pacchimaṃ dvāraṃ apāpurīyati … pe … "
msgstr "There comes a time when, after a very long period has passed, the western gate … "

msgctxt "mn130:18.7"
msgid "uttaraṃ dvāraṃ apāpurīyati … pe … "
msgstr "northern gate … "

msgctxt "mn130:18.8"
msgid "dakkhiṇaṃ dvāraṃ apāpurīyati. "
msgstr "southern gate of the Great hell is opened. "

msgctxt "mn130:18.9"
msgid "So tattha sīghena javena dhāvati. "
msgstr "So they run there as fast as they can. "

msgctxt "mn130:18.10"
msgid "Tassa sīghena javena dhāvato chavimpi ḍayhati, cammampi ḍayhati, maṃsampi ḍayhati, nhārumpi ḍayhati, aṭṭhīnipi sampadhūpāyanti, ubbhataṃ tādisameva hoti. "
msgstr "And as they run, their outer skin, inner skin, flesh, and sinews burn and even their bones smoke. Such is their escape; "

msgctxt "mn130:18.11"
msgid "Yato ca kho so, bhikkhave, bahusampatto hoti, atha taṃ dvāraṃ pidhīyati. "
msgstr "but when they’ve managed to make it most of the way, the gate is slammed shut. "

msgctxt "mn130:18.12"
msgid "So tattha dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedeti, na ca tāva kālaṃ karoti yāva na taṃ pāpakammaṃ byantīhoti. "
msgstr "And there they feel painful, sharp, severe, acute feelings—but they don’t die until that bad deed is eliminated. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya19, sc29
msgctxt "mn130:19.1"
msgid "Hoti kho so, bhikkhave, samayo yaṃ kadāci karahaci dīghassa addhuno accayena tassa mahānirayassa puratthimaṃ dvāraṃ apāpurīyati. "
msgstr "There comes a time when, after a very long period has passed, the eastern gate of the Great Hell is opened. "

msgctxt "mn130:19.2"
msgid "So tattha sīghena javena dhāvati. "
msgstr "So they run there as fast as they can. "

msgctxt "mn130:19.3"
msgid "Tassa sīghena javena dhāvato chavimpi ḍayhati, cammampi ḍayhati, maṃsampi ḍayhati, nhārumpi ḍayhati, aṭṭhīnipi sampadhūpāyanti, ubbhataṃ tādisameva hoti. "
msgstr "And as they run, their outer skin, inner skin, flesh, and sinews burn and even their bones smoke. Such is their escape; "

msgctxt "mn130:19.4"
msgid "So tena dvārena nikkhamati. "
msgstr "and they make it out that door. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya20, pts-vp-pli3.185, sc30
msgctxt "mn130:20.1"
msgid "Tassa kho pana, bhikkhave, mahānirayassa samanantarā sahitameva mahanto gūthanirayo. "
msgstr "Immediately adjacent to the Great Hell is the vast Dung Hell. "

msgctxt "mn130:20.2"
msgid "So tattha patati. "
msgstr "And that’s where they fall. "

msgctxt "mn130:20.3"
msgid "Tasmiṃ kho pana, bhikkhave, gūthaniraye sūcimukhā pāṇā chaviṃ chindanti, chaviṃ chetvā cammaṃ chindanti, cammaṃ chetvā maṃsaṃ chindanti, maṃsaṃ chetvā nhāruṃ chindanti, nhāruṃ chetvā aṭṭhiṃ chindanti, aṭṭhiṃ chetvā aṭṭhimiñjaṃ khādanti. "
msgstr "In that Dung Hell there are needle-mouthed creatures that bore through the outer skin, the inner skin, the flesh, sinews, and bones, until they reach the marrow and devour it. "

msgctxt "mn130:20.4"
msgid "So tattha dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedeti, na ca tāva kālaṃ karoti yāva na taṃ pāpakammaṃ byantīhoti. (1) "
msgstr "And there they feel painful, sharp, severe, acute feelings—but they don’t die until that bad deed is eliminated. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya21, sc31
msgctxt "mn130:21.1"
msgid "Tassa kho pana, bhikkhave, gūthanirayassa samanantarā sahitameva mahanto kukkulanirayo. "
msgstr "Immediately adjacent to the Dung Hell is the vast Hell of Hot Coals. "

msgctxt "mn130:21.2"
msgid "So tattha patati. "
msgstr "And that’s where they fall. "

msgctxt "mn130:21.3"
msgid "So tattha dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedeti, na ca tāva kālaṃ karoti yāva na taṃ pāpakammaṃ byantīhoti. (2) "
msgstr "And there they feel painful, sharp, severe, acute feelings—but they don’t die until that bad deed is eliminated. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya22, sc32
#. VAR: uddhaṃ → uccaṃ (s1-3, km) | ubbhato (mr)
msgctxt "mn130:22.1"
msgid "Tassa kho pana, bhikkhave, kukkulanirayassa samanantarā sahitameva mahantaṃ simbalivanaṃ uddhaṃ yojanamuggataṃ soḷasaṅgulakaṇṭakaṃ ādittaṃ sampajjalitaṃ sajotibhūtaṃ. "
msgstr "Immediately adjacent to the Hell of Hot Coals is the vast Hell of the Red Silk-Cotton Wood. It’s a league high, full of sixteen-inch thorns, burning, blazing, and glowing. "

msgctxt "mn130:22.2"
msgid "Tattha āropentipi oropentipi. "
msgstr "And there they make them climb up and down. "

msgctxt "mn130:22.3"
msgid "So tattha dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedeti, na ca tāva kālaṃ karoti yāva na taṃ pāpakammaṃ byantīhoti. (3) "
msgstr "And there they feel painful, sharp, severe, acute feelings—but they don’t die until that bad deed is eliminated. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya23, sc33
msgctxt "mn130:23.1"
msgid "Tassa kho pana, bhikkhave, simbalivanassa samanantarā sahitameva mahantaṃ asipattavanaṃ. "
msgstr "Immediately adjacent to the Hell of the Red Silk-Cotton Wood is the vast Hell of the Sword-Leaf Trees. "

msgctxt "mn130:23.2"
msgid "So tattha pavisati. "
msgstr "They enter that. "

msgctxt "mn130:23.3"
msgid "Tassa vāteritāni pattāni patitāni hatthampi chindanti, pādampi chindanti, hatthapādampi chindanti, kaṇṇampi chindanti, nāsampi chindanti, kaṇṇanāsampi chindanti. "
msgstr "There the fallen leaves blown by the wind cut their hands, feet, both hands and feet; they cut their ears, nose, both ears and nose. "

msgctxt "mn130:23.4"
msgid "So tattha dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedeti, na ca tāva kālaṃ karoti yāva na taṃ pāpakammaṃ byantīhoti. (4) "
msgstr "And there they feel painful, sharp, severe, acute feelings—but they don’t die until that bad deed is eliminated. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya24, sc34
#. VAR: khārodakā nadī → khārodikā nadī (bj)
msgctxt "mn130:24.1"
msgid "Tassa kho pana, bhikkhave, asipattavanassa samanantarā sahitameva mahatī khārodakā nadī. "
msgstr "Immediately adjacent to the Hell of the Sword-Leaf Trees is the vast Acid Hell. "

msgctxt "mn130:24.2"
msgid "So tattha patati. "
msgstr "And that’s where they fall. "

msgctxt "mn130:24.3"
msgid "So tattha anusotampi vuyhati, paṭisotampi vuyhati, anusotapaṭisotampi vuyhati. "
msgstr "There they are swept upstream, swept downstream, and swept both up and down stream. "

msgctxt "mn130:24.4"
msgid "So tattha dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedeti, na ca tāva kālaṃ karoti yāva na taṃ pāpakammaṃ byantīhoti. (5) "
msgstr "And there they feel painful, sharp, severe, acute feelings—but they don’t die until that bad deed is eliminated. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya25, pts-vp-pli3.186, sc35
msgctxt "mn130:25.1"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, nirayapālā balisena uddharitvā thale patiṭṭhāpetvā evamāhaṃsu: "
msgstr "Then the wardens of hell pull them out and place them on dry land, and say, "

msgctxt "mn130:25.2"
msgid "‘ambho purisa, kiṃ icchasī’ti? "
msgstr "‘Mister, what do you want?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn130:25.3"
msgid "So evamāha: "
msgstr "They say, "

msgctxt "mn130:25.4"
msgid "‘jighacchitosmi, bhante’ti. "
msgstr "‘I’m hungry, sir.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn130:25.5"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, nirayapālā tattena ayosaṅkunā mukhaṃ vivaritvā ādittena sampajjalitena sajotibhūtena tattaṃ lohaguḷaṃ mukhe pakkhipanti ādittaṃ sampajjalitaṃ sajotibhūtaṃ. "
msgstr "The wardens of hell force open their mouth with a hot iron spike—burning, blazing, glowing—and shove in a red-hot copper ball, burning, blazing, and glowing. "

#. VAR: tassa → tassa (si, pts1) | taṃ tassa (mr)
#. VAR: dahati → ḍayhati (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
#. VAR: urampi → udarampi (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "mn130:25.6"
msgid "So tassa oṭṭhampi dahati, mukhampi dahati, kaṇṭhampi dahati, urampi dahati, antampi antaguṇampi ādāya adhobhāgā nikkhamati. "
msgstr "It burns their lips, mouth, tongue, throat, and stomach before coming out below dragging their entrails. "

msgctxt "mn130:25.7"
msgid "So tattha dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedeti, na ca tāva kālaṃ karoti yāva na taṃ pāpakammaṃ byantīhoti. "
msgstr "And there they feel painful, sharp, severe, acute feelings—but they don’t die until that bad deed is eliminated. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya26, sc36
msgctxt "mn130:26.1"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, nirayapālā evamāhaṃsu: "
msgstr "Then the wardens of hell say, "

msgctxt "mn130:26.2"
msgid "‘ambho purisa, kiṃ icchasī’ti? "
msgstr "‘Mister, what do you want?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn130:26.3"
msgid "So evamāha: "
msgstr "They say, "

msgctxt "mn130:26.4"
msgid "‘pipāsitosmi, bhante’ti. "
msgstr "‘I’m thirsty, sir.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn130:26.5"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, nirayapālā tattena ayosaṅkunā mukhaṃ vivaritvā ādittena sampajjalitena sajotibhūtena tattaṃ tambalohaṃ mukhe āsiñcanti ādittaṃ sampajjalitaṃ sajotibhūtaṃ. "
msgstr "The wardens of hell force open their mouth with a hot iron spike—burning, blazing, glowing—and pour in molten copper, burning, blazing, and glowing. "

#. VAR: tassa → ettha pana pāṭhabhedo
msgctxt "mn130:26.6"
msgid "Taṃ tassa oṭṭhampi dahati, mukhampi dahati, kaṇṭhampi dahati, urampi dahati, antampi antaguṇampi ādāya adhobhāgā nikkhamati. "
msgstr "It burns their lips, mouth, tongue, throat, and stomach before coming out below dragging their entrails. "

msgctxt "mn130:26.7"
msgid "So tattha dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedeti, na ca tāva kālaṃ karoti, yāva na taṃ pāpakammaṃ byantīhoti. "
msgstr "And there they feel painful, sharp, severe, acute feelings—but they don’t die until that bad deed is eliminated. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya27
msgctxt "mn130:27.1"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, nirayapālā puna mahāniraye pakkhipanti. "
msgstr "Then the wardens of hell toss them back in the Great Hell. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya28, sc37
msgctxt "mn130:28.1"
msgid "Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, yamassa rañño etadahosi: "
msgstr "Once upon a time, King Yama thought: "

msgctxt "mn130:28.2"
msgid "‘ye kira, bho, loke pāpakāni akusalāni kammāni karonti te evarūpā vividhā kammakāraṇā karīyanti. "
msgstr "‘Those who do such bad deeds in the world receive these many different punishments. "

msgctxt "mn130:28.3"
msgid "Aho vatāhaṃ manussattaṃ labheyyaṃ. Tathāgato ca loke uppajjeyya arahaṃ sammāsambuddho. Tañcāhaṃ bhagavantaṃ payirupāseyyaṃ. "
msgstr "Oh, I hope I may be reborn as a human being! And that a Realized One—a perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha—arises in the world! And that I may pay homage to the Buddha! "

msgctxt "mn130:28.4"
msgid "So ca me bhagavā dhammaṃ deseyya. Tassa cāhaṃ bhagavato dhammaṃ ājāneyyan’ti. "
msgstr "Then the Buddha can teach me Dhamma, so that I may understand his teaching.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya29
msgctxt "mn130:29.1"
msgid "Taṃ kho panāhaṃ, bhikkhave, nāññassa samaṇassa vā brāhmaṇassa vā sutvā vadāmi, api ca yadeva sāmaṃ ñātaṃ sāmaṃ diṭṭhaṃ sāmaṃ viditaṃ tadevāhaṃ vadāmī”ti. "
msgstr "Now, I don’t say this because I’ve heard it from some other ascetic or brahmin. I only say it because I’ve known, seen, and realized it for myself.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya30, pts-vp-pli3.187, sc38
msgctxt "mn130:30.1"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā. "
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said. "

#. VAR: Idaṃ vatvāna → idaṃ vatvā (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "mn130:30.2"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā: "
msgstr "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc39
msgctxt "mn130:30.3"
msgid "“Coditā devadūtehi, "
msgstr "“Those people who are negligent, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn130:30.4"
msgid "ye pamajjanti māṇavā; "
msgstr "when warned by the gods’ messengers: "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn130:30.5"
msgid "Te dīgharattaṃ socanti, "
msgstr "a long time they sorrow, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn130:30.6"
msgid "hīnakāyūpagā narā. "
msgstr "when they go to that wretched place. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc40
msgctxt "mn130:30.7"
msgid "Ye ca kho devadūtehi, "
msgstr "But those good and peaceful people, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn130:30.8"
msgid "santo sappurisā idha; "
msgstr "when warned by the gods’ messengers, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn130:30.9"
msgid "Coditā nappamajjanti, "
msgstr "never neglect "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn130:30.10"
msgid "ariyadhamme kudācanaṃ. "
msgstr "the teaching of the noble ones. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc41
msgctxt "mn130:30.11"
msgid "Upādāne bhayaṃ disvā, "
msgstr "Seeing the danger in grasping, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn130:30.12"
msgid "jātimaraṇasambhave; "
msgstr "the origin of birth and death, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn130:30.13"
msgid "Anupādā vimuccanti, "
msgstr "they’re freed by not grasping, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn130:30.14"
msgid "jātimaraṇasaṅkhaye. "
msgstr "with the ending of birth and death. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc42
msgctxt "mn130:30.15"
msgid "Te khemappattā sukhino, "
msgstr "Happy, they’ve come to a safe place, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn130:30.16"
msgid "diṭṭhadhammābhinibbutā; "
msgstr "extinguished in this very life. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn130:30.17"
msgid "Sabbaverabhayātītā, "
msgstr "They’ve gone beyond all threats and perils, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: sabbadukkhaṃ → sabbadukkhā (mr)
msgctxt "mn130:30.18"
msgid "sabbadukkhaṃ upaccagun”ti. "
msgstr "and risen above all suffering.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn130:30.19"
msgid "Devadūtasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "mn130:30.20"
msgid "Suññatavaggo niṭṭhito tatiyo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc43
msgctxt "mn130:30.21"
msgid "Dvidhāva suññatā hoti, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn130:30.22"
msgid "Abbhutadhammabākulaṃ; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn130:30.23"
msgid "Aciravatabhūmijanāmo, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn130:30.24"
msgid "Anuruddhupakkilesaṃ; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn130:30.25"
msgid "Bālapaṇḍito devadūtañca te dasāti. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
